content:
Certainly! Here's a simple HTML code snippet for a birthday wish card that includes a personalized message and a picture:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Birthday Wish Card</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f0f8ff;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
        }
        .card {
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            width: 300px;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .card img {
            width: 100%;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        .message {
            margin-top: 15px;
            font-size: 1.2em;
            color: #333;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="card">
        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/300x200" alt="Birthday Image">
        <div class="message">
            <p>Happy Birthday, [Name]!</p>
            <p>Wishing you a day filled with love and joy!</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

In this code snippet, replace `[Name]` with the recipient's name and update the `src` attribute of the `<img>` tag with the URL of the picture you want to use. This will create a simple and elegant birthday wish card with a personalized message.
